1070","Holkham, Norfolk, England":"Holkham, Norfolk, England","Lavendon, Buckinghamshire, England":"Lavendon, Buckinghamshire, England","Holkham, Norfolk, England.":"Holkham, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Ewyas, Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"about 1090–1185":"circa 1090–1185","1090–1185":"1090–1185","1070–1129":"1070–1129","1128–1180":"1128–1180","1079–1185":"1079–1185","–1130":"–1130","1129":"1129","1128":"1128","1090":"1090","about 1090":"circa 1090","about 1180":"circa 1180","1079":"1079","about 1128":"circa 1128","after 1130":"na 1130","1185":"1185","1130":"1130","1180":"1180","1070":"1070","Holkham, Norfolk, England":"Holkham, Norfolk, England","Lavendon, Buckinghamshire, England":"Lavendon, Buckinghamshire, England","Holkham, Norfolk, England.":"Holkham, Norfolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Ewyas, Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"about 1090–1185":"about 1090–1185","1090–1185":"1090–1185","1070–1129":"1070–1129","1128–1180":"1128–1180","1079–1185":"1079–1185","–1130":"–1130","1129":"1129","1128":"1128","1090":"1090","about 1090":"about 1090","about 1180":"about 1180","1079":"1079","about 1128":"about 1128","after 1130":"after 1130","1185":"1185","1130":"1130","1180":"1180","1070":"1070","Holkham, Norfolk, England":"Holkham, Norfolk, England","Lavendon, Buckinghamshire, England":"Lavendon, Buckinghamshire, England","Holkham, Norfolk, England.":"Holkham, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Ewyas, Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bidun","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Hampshire and Surrey): habitational name, probably from Baydon (Wiltshire). The placename may have meant ‘hill associated with a woman named Bēage’ (a personal name derived from Old English <i>bēag</i> ‘ring, bracelet, torque’ + Old English <i>dūn</i>). The surname is pronounced /'baidən/.","History: The surname <i>Biden</i> has a long history in East Meon (Hampshire), recorded there from 1327 until at least the 1840s. — Joe Biden, the 46th president of the US, is of Irish, English, and French descent. His mother’s Jean (Catherine Eugenia) Finnegan entire family tree traces back to Ireland, with some of the ancestors named Blewitt (see   Blewett  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Blewett","meanings":["English and Irish (of Norman origin): nickname from Old French <i>bleuet</i>, <i>blouet</i> ‘bluish’, a diminutive of <i>bleu</i> ‘blue’, more specifically ‘pale, pallid, wan’, or ‘fair-haired, golden-haired’. Compare   Blew  ,   Blewitt  , and   Bluett  .","History: The Norman Ralph Bloet is mentioned in Domesday Book (1086) as lord of the manor of Hinton in Hampshire, recorded in 1246 as <i>Henton Bluet</i> (modern Hinton Blewett). From the late 12th century onward many Anglo-Norman knights acquired estates in Ireland. Ralph's presumed descendants, Thomas and Ralph Bluet, held lands in counties Cork and Limerick before and after 1254, and are ancestors of the modern Irish families named Bluett, Blewett, and Blewitt. In 1850, following the Irish Potato Famine in Ireland (1845–49), Patrick Blewitt, a son of Edward Blewitt of Ballina, County Mayo, migrated to North America, his whole family joining him in 1851 to settle in Scranton PA. Joe Biden (see   Biden  ), the 46th president of the US, is Edward's great-great-great grandson."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Bright’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Hanelade de Bidun was born about 1090, in Holkham, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom as the son of Hanelade Bidun and Sara of Lavendon. He had at least 1 son with Agnes FitzJohn. He died in 1185, in his hometown, at the age of 96."},"et":{"about 1090–1185":"umbes 1090–1185","1090–1185":"1090–1185","1070–1129":"1070–1129","1128–1180":"